Crimes That Shook Australia - S02E06 - Raechel Betts

The murder of Raechel Betts in 2009 sent shock waves through Australia, particularly because of the gruesome nature of the crime. John Coombes strangled Raechel Betts in a Port Phillip home and then dismembered her body and threw her limbs into the sea. Prior to the murder of Raechel Betts, John Coombes had a long criminal history, including escapes from jail and two other murders.
